 {"id":"bd-2nt4","title":"Unit tests for atomic rate limiter","description":"## Purpose\nComprehensive unit tests for the atomic rate limiter (tryConsume method), ensuring no race conditions under concurrent access.\n\n## Test File Location\n`apps/gateway/src/middleware/__tests__/rate-limit.test.ts`\n\n## Test Cases\n\n### 1. Basic Functionality\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"InMemoryRateLimiter.tryConsume - basic operations\", () => {\n  let limiter: InMemoryRateLimiter;\n\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter();\n    console.log(\"[TEST] Created fresh limiter instance\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"should allow first request and consume slot\", () => {\n    const config = { limit: 10, windowMs: 60000 };\n    const result = limiter.tryConsume(\"test-key\", config);\n    \n    expect(result.allowed).toBe(true);\n    expect(result.info.remaining).toBe(9);\n    expect(result.info.limit).toBe(10);\n    expect(result.info.exceeded).toBe(false);\n    console.log(`[TEST] First request: allowed=${result.allowed}, remaining=${result.info.remaining}`);\n  });\n\n  it(\"should correctly decrement remaining with each request\", () => {\n    const config = { limit: 5, windowMs: 60000 };\n    \n    for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n      const result = limiter.tryConsume(\"test-key\", config);\n      expect(result.info.remaining).toBe(4 - i);\n      console.log(`[TEST] Request ${i + 1}: remaining=${result.info.remaining}`);\n    }\n  });\n\n  it(\"should deny request when limit reached\", () => {\n    const config = { limit: 3, windowMs: 60000 };\n    \n    // Consume all slots\n    for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {\n      limiter.tryConsume(\"test-key\", config);\n    }\n    \n    // Next request should be denied\n    const result = limiter.tryConsume(\"test-key\", config);\n    expect(result.allowed).toBe(false);\n    expect(result.info.remaining).toBe(0);\n    expect(result.info.exceeded).toBe(true);\n    console.log(\"[TEST] PASS: Request denied when limit reached\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"should NOT consume slot when denied\", () => {\n    const config = { limit: 2, windowMs: 60000 };\n    \n    // Hit the limit\n    limiter.tryConsume(\"test-key\", config);\n    limiter.tryConsume(\"test-key\", config);\n    \n    // Try 10 more times - count should stay at 2\n    for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {\n      const result = limiter.tryConsume(\"test-key\", config);\n      expect(result.allowed).toBe(false);\n    }\n    \n    // Internal count should still be 2, not 12\n    const info = limiter.peek(\"test-key\", config);\n    expect(info.remaining).toBe(0);\n    console.log(\"[TEST] PASS: Denied requests do not consume slots\");\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### 2. Window Reset Behavior\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"InMemoryRateLimiter.tryConsume - window reset\", () => {\n  it(\"should reset counter after window expires\", async () => {\n    jest.useFakeTimers();\n    const limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter();\n    const config = { limit: 1, windowMs: 1000 };\n    \n    // Use the one allowed request\n    let result = limiter.tryConsume(\"test-key\", config);\n    expect(result.allowed).toBe(true);\n    \n    // Should be denied now\n    result = limiter.tryConsume(\"test-key\", config);\n    expect(result.allowed).toBe(false);\n    console.log(\"[TEST] Request denied before window reset\");\n    \n    // Advance past window\n    jest.advanceTimersByTime(1001);\n    \n    // Should be allowed again\n    result = limiter.tryConsume(\"test-key\", config);\n    expect(result.allowed).toBe(true);\n    expect(result.info.remaining).toBe(0);  // Used the new slot\n    console.log(\"[TEST] PASS: Window reset allows new requests\");\n    \n    jest.useRealTimers();\n  });\n\n  it(\"should provide correct reset timestamp\", () => {\n    const limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter();\n    const config = { limit: 10, windowMs: 60000 };\n    const beforeRequest = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);\n    \n    const result = limiter.tryConsume(\"test-key\", config);\n    \n    // Reset should be ~60 seconds from now\n    expect(result.info.reset).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(beforeRequest + 59);\n    expect(result.info.reset).toBeLessThanOrEqual(beforeRequest + 61);\n    console.log(`[TEST] Reset timestamp: ${result.info.reset} (now+60s)`);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### 3. Multi-Key Independence\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"InMemoryRateLimiter.tryConsume - key isolation\", () => {\n  it(\"should track different keys independently\", () => {\n    const limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter();\n    const config = { limit: 2, windowMs: 60000 };\n    \n    // Exhaust key1\n    limiter.tryConsume(\"key1\", config);\n    limiter.tryConsume(\"key1\", config);\n    \n    // key1 should be denied\n    expect(limiter.tryConsume(\"key1\", config).allowed).toBe(false);\n    \n    // key2 should still work\n    expect(limiter.tryConsume(\"key2\", config).allowed).toBe(true);\n    expect(limiter.tryConsume(\"key2\", config).allowed).toBe(true);\n    expect(limiter.tryConsume(\"key2\", config).allowed).toBe(false);\n    \n    console.log(\"[TEST] PASS: Keys are isolated\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"should handle many concurrent keys\", () => {\n    const limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter(60000, 10000);\n    const config = { limit: 1, windowMs: 60000 };\n    \n    // Create 1000 different keys\n    for (let i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {\n      const result = limiter.tryConsume(`key-${i}`, config);\n      expect(result.allowed).toBe(true);\n    }\n    \n    expect(limiter.size()).toBe(1000);\n    console.log(`[TEST] PASS: Handled 1000 distinct keys`);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### 4. Concurrency Simulation (CRITICAL)\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"InMemoryRateLimiter.tryConsume - concurrency\", () => {\n  it(\"should allow exactly limit requests under concurrent load\", async () => {\n    const limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter();\n    const config = { limit: 100, windowMs: 60000 };\n    const startTime = Date.now();\n    \n    // Simulate 1000 concurrent requests\n    const promises = Array.from({ length: 1000 }, () =>\n      Promise.resolve(limiter.tryConsume(\"burst-key\", config))\n    );\n    \n    const results = await Promise.all(promises);\n    const elapsed = Date.now() - startTime;\n    \n    const allowed = results.filter(r => r.allowed).length;\n    const denied = results.filter(r => !r.allowed).length;\n    \n    console.log(`[TEST] Concurrent test: ${allowed} allowed, ${denied} denied in ${elapsed}ms`);\n    \n    // CRITICAL: Exactly 100 should be allowed, not more\n    expect(allowed).toBe(100);\n    expect(denied).toBe(900);\n    console.log(\"[TEST] PASS: No race condition - exactly limit requests allowed\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"should handle interleaved requests across multiple keys\", async () => {\n    const limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter();\n    const config = { limit: 10, windowMs: 60000 };\n    \n    // Interleave requests across 10 keys\n    const promises = Array.from({ length: 500 }, (_, i) =>\n      Promise.resolve(limiter.tryConsume(`key-${i % 10}`, config))\n    );\n    \n    const results = await Promise.all(promises);\n    const allowedByKey = new Map<string, number>();\n    \n    results.forEach((r, i) => {\n      const key = `key-${i % 10}`;\n      if (r.allowed) {\n        allowedByKey.set(key, (allowedByKey.get(key) || 0) + 1);\n      }\n    });\n    \n    // Each key should have exactly 10 allowed\n    for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {\n      expect(allowedByKey.get(`key-${i}`)).toBe(10);\n    }\n    console.log(\"[TEST] PASS: Interleaved requests handled correctly\");\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### 5. Memory Management\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"InMemoryRateLimiter - memory management\", () => {\n  it(\"should enforce maxItems limit\", () => {\n    const limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter(60000, 100);  // maxItems=100\n    const config = { limit: 10, windowMs: 60000 };\n    \n    // Create 200 keys\n    for (let i = 0; i < 200; i++) {\n      limiter.tryConsume(`key-${i}`, config);\n    }\n    \n    // Should be limited to 100\n    expect(limiter.size()).toBeLessThanOrEqual(100);\n    console.log(`[TEST] Size after 200 keys: ${limiter.size()}`);\n  });\n\n  it(\"should cleanup expired entries\", async () => {\n    jest.useFakeTimers();\n    const limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter(100, 1000);  // cleanup every 100ms\n    const config = { limit: 10, windowMs: 500 };  // 500ms window\n    \n    // Create entries\n    limiter.tryConsume(\"key1\", config);\n    limiter.tryConsume(\"key2\", config);\n    expect(limiter.size()).toBe(2);\n    \n    // Advance past window expiry\n    jest.advanceTimersByTime(600);\n    \n    // Manual cleanup\n    const removed = limiter.cleanup();\n    expect(removed).toBe(2);\n    expect(limiter.size()).toBe(0);\n    console.log(`[TEST] Cleanup removed ${removed} expired entries`);\n    \n    jest.useRealTimers();\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### 6. Edge Cases\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"InMemoryRateLimiter.tryConsume - edge cases\", () => {\n  it(\"should handle limit of 0 (always deny)\", () => {\n    const limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter();\n    const config = { limit: 0, windowMs: 60000 };\n    \n    const result = limiter.tryConsume(\"test\", config);\n    expect(result.allowed).toBe(false);\n    console.log(\"[TEST] PASS: limit=0 always denies\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"should handle limit of 1\", () => {\n    const limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter();\n    const config = { limit: 1, windowMs: 60000 };\n    \n    expect(limiter.tryConsume(\"test\", config).allowed).toBe(true);\n    expect(limiter.tryConsume(\"test\", config).allowed).toBe(false);\n    console.log(\"[TEST] PASS: limit=1 allows exactly one request\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"should handle very large limits\", () => {\n    const limiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter();\n    const config = { limit: 1000000, windowMs: 60000 };\n    \n    const result = limiter.tryConsume(\"test\", config);\n    expect(result.allowed).toBe(true);\n    expect(result.info.remaining).toBe(999999);\n    console.log(\"[TEST] PASS: Large limits handled\");\n  });\n});\n```\n\n## Logging Requirements\n- Log result of each request (allowed, remaining)\n- Log timing for concurrent tests\n- Log memory stats for cleanup tests\n- Log PASS/FAIL for each test\n\n## CI Integration\n```yaml\n- name: Run rate limiter unit tests\n  run: pnpm test apps/gateway/src/middleware/__tests__/rate-limit.test.ts --coverage\n```\n\n## Coverage Requirements\n- tryConsume: 100%\n- cleanup: 100%\n- enforceMaxItems: 100%\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Basic allow/deny logic works\n- [ ] Window reset works correctly\n- [ ] Keys are independent\n- [ ] Exactly limit requests allowed under concurrency\n- [ ] Memory limits enforced\n- [ ] Edge cases handled\n- [ ] All logging assertions pass","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T23:31:26.332797359Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T23:54:03.022355564Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T23:41:19.160042630Z","close_reason":"Already completed as part of bd-11wh fix - tests for tryConsume() including basic functionality, window reset, multiple keys, concurrency simulation, and rate limit info are all in rate-limit.middleware.test.ts (commit 35d2feb)","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2nt4","depends_on_id":"bd-11wh","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T23:31:26.347136936Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
